          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE",
                "BGO"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "The Gamma-ray ER coincidences were mea-",
                "sured using first a high resolution HPGe detector and",
                "subsequently with an array of 14 BGO detectors. The",
                "HPGe data were used to determine the absolute ER",
                "detection efficiencies of HIRA which were in",
                "agreement with those extracted from the measured",
                "charge, energy, and angular distributions of ER.",
                "The BGO array was used to measure Gamma-ray fold",
                "distribution in coincidence with the ER at the",
                "focal plane."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC",
                "ASEP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "-All the measurements utilized the",
                "sliding seal target chamber of the recoil mass",
                "separator HIRA (Heavy Ion Recoil Analyser) with the",
                "chamber modified with special bucket structures from",
                "top and bottom plates to accommodate Gamma detectors",
                "in close geometry. A thin carbon foil was used for",
                "charge-state reequilibration before the recoiling",
                "ER enter HIRA."
              ]
            }
          ],
